"Pours to a thin, cream-colored head with minimal lacing.  The color is black and opaque.  Held up to the light, slight reddish brown hues become visible from the black.  The aroma is mild, with a malty, chocolate type of odor.  Creamy in texture, with a malty, chocolate type of flavor up front and a moderate coffee bitterness finish.  Pretty full-bodied, especially for a beer with such low carbonation.  Good price too.  Purchased for $1.59 a bottle or $8.99 build your own 6-pack."
