"I was very excited to try this beer, as I have never been let down by a Southern Tier offering (so obviously I enjoy the sweetness they add to their beers).  This one is interesting enough, but I see it as nothing more than a creative recipe that is fun to try, but doesn't exactly leave you wanting more.  The taste of the beer seemed very artificial to me.  You can definitely taste all the flavors advertised, I am just of the opinion that it's not very well done.  The coffee is definitely there, as is the lemon peel, they just feel fake and the thinness of the beer does not help the cause.  Overall, this is just an average beer to me, but fun to try if you are sick of traditional style stouts/porters."
"O - A very interesting beer, with strong black coffee roots, but enough malt, caramel, and chocolate notes to keep things varied and interesting.  A touch more bitter than my favorite coffee brews, it still works well and offers a nice contrast to other stouts."
