"12 ounce bottle, looks like the bottled on date is 12/04/14.  Served in a nonic pint glass, the beer pours dark brown/black with about an inch light tan head.  Head retention and lacing are both decent enough.  The brew smells like coffee, caramel, chocolate, lemon peel and lactose/sugar.  I think the taste is just like the aroma, with the coffee, chocolate, lactose and caramel flavors being the strongest, but with the lemon peel/citrus definitely noticeable too.  Mouthfeel/body is medium, it's a bit creamy with moderate carbonation.  I wasn't sure how the lemon peel/citrus would work with a milk stout, but I think it turned out good.  It's worth trying at least once, I know I wouldn't mind trying this again.  $1.84 for a single bottle."
