"Overall I thought this was a decent beer and I think it's a decent example of a Coffee Stout, but in the end I found it to taste more like regular black coffee than a espresso and the aroma made this beer rough around the edges.  This beer had ok drinkability, it was smooth, a little crisp, a little creamy, not too filling and the taste didn't do the best job at holding my attention, I think one would be my limit, any more than that and I might start to get bored with it.  What I like the most about this beer was the appearance and mouthfeel, they were both good and to me they were the highlights of this beer.  What I liked the least about this beer was the aroma, it wasn't good and it had some off aspects to it.  I wouldn't buy this beer again, it was nice to try once, but it isn't something that I feel the need to revisit any time soon.  If you really like Coffee Stouts it might be worth a try, but i wouldn't recommend it as a standout example of the style.  All in all this wasn't bad beer, but in the end I just wasn't a big fan of it and I found the off aromas to be a little surprising.  It's not a favorite beer from this brewery and it's not a favorite for the style either.  This beer just wasn't for me and I think it could use a little bit of work, better luck next time guys."
